##########################################################################################################################
# 1. Get some info
#    - username
#    - hostname
#    - current shell
#    - date/time
#    - date as "day-month-year"
#    - date as seconds only
#    - current directory
#    - content of your home directory
#    - existence of the file named ".bashrc" in your home directory
#    - get statistics of your .bashrc file
#    - how many chars/words/lines in your .bashrc file
#    - how many hidden items (files, dirs, ...) do you have in your home ?
#    - how many hidden directories do you have in your home ?
#    - how many commands started with the letter "c" can you invoke ?
#    - can you invoke the tool named "calibre". Whence ?
##########################################################################################################################

##########################################################################################################################
# 2. Create/Copy/Edit
#    - cd to your home dir
#    - remove the dir named "training" independent of existence
